CHECK:SPACING: spaces preferred around that '-' (ctx:VxV)
#127: FILE: lib/idr.c:124:
+			p = pa[l-1];
 			        ^

Whitespace style used in the kernel sources is described in kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'id >= MAX_ID_BIT'
#128: FILE: lib/idr.c:125:
+			if ((id >= MAX_ID_BIT) || (id < 0))

Parentheses are not required in the following cases:

  1. Function pointer uses::

      (foo->bar)();

    could be::

      foo->bar();

  2. Comparisons in if::

      if ((foo->bar) && (foo->baz))
      if ((foo == bar))

    could be::

      if (foo->bar && foo->baz)
      if (foo == bar)

  3. addressof/dereference single Lvalues::

      &(foo->bar)
      *(foo->bar)

    could be::

      &foo->bar
      *foo->bar

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'id < 0'
#128: FILE: lib/idr.c:125:
+			if ((id >= MAX_ID_BIT) || (id < 0))

ERROR:ASSIGN_IN_IF: do not use assignment in if condition
#148: FILE: lib/idr.c:168:
+		if (!(p = pa[l++]))

Do not use assignments in if condition.
Example::

  if ((foo = bar(...)) < BAZ) {

should be written as::

  foo = bar(...);
  if (foo < BAZ) {

